WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.505 --> 00:00:02.002
- HI, I'm Priscilla Chan.

00:00:02.002 --> 00:00:04.348
- And I'm Sal Khan, and
we're here to announce

00:00:04.348 --> 00:00:06.588
the Breakthrough Junior Challenge.

00:00:06.588 --> 00:00:07.761
For those of you who don't know,

00:00:07.761 --> 00:00:10.721
the Breakthrough Prize,
is a prize to the world's

00:00:10.721 --> 00:00:12.930
top mathematicians and scientists

00:00:12.930 --> 00:00:14.437
for discoveries that are going to

00:00:14.437 --> 00:00:16.480
change the world around us.

00:00:16.480 --> 00:00:18.686
And the Breakthrough Junior Challenge

00:00:18.686 --> 00:00:21.484
is to reach out to high school students,

00:00:21.484 --> 00:00:23.318
with the recognition that
the biggest breakthroughs

00:00:23.318 --> 00:00:25.861
start with an insight, with a
new way of looking at things.

00:00:25.861 --> 00:00:28.020
It could be existing
discoveries or theories,

00:00:28.020 --> 00:00:29.205
it could be a recent one,

00:00:29.205 --> 00:00:32.441
or it could be something that
you discover on your own.

00:00:32.441 --> 00:00:33.663
- We want to hear from you.

00:00:33.663 --> 00:00:36.914
All you scientists, tinkers,
innovators in the world,

00:00:36.914 --> 00:00:38.539
send us your video.

00:00:38.539 --> 00:00:41.465
We want to hear from you by October 7th,

00:00:41.465 --> 00:00:43.636
in a short video where you explain

00:00:43.636 --> 00:00:46.178
what you're excited about these days.

00:00:46.178 --> 00:00:47.641
- And what do they win?

00:00:47.641 --> 00:00:50.602
- This is pretty exciting in itself.

00:00:50.602 --> 00:00:52.355
You'll win a college scholarship,

00:00:52.355 --> 00:00:54.630
your teacher will get a prize for being

00:00:54.630 --> 00:00:56.801
such an important mentor in your life,

00:00:56.801 --> 00:01:00.470
and your school gets a
brand new lab for everyone

00:01:00.470 --> 00:01:02.897
to be able to work hands-on
and learn about science.

00:01:02.897 --> 00:01:04.534
- [Sal] And they get to fly out here.

00:01:04.534 --> 00:01:06.229
- Oh yea, this is the most glamorous

00:01:06.229 --> 00:01:08.154
science event in the world.

00:01:08.154 --> 00:01:09.480
Best science fair ever.

00:01:09.480 --> 00:01:11.117
- And we can't wait to
see what you produce.

00:01:11.117 --> 00:01:13.369
We suspect that you're
going to blow our minds,

00:01:13.369 --> 00:01:15.377
and open many, many more people's minds

00:01:15.377 --> 00:01:18.001
to the magic of science
that will eventually lead

00:01:18.001 --> 00:01:19.464
to future breakthroughs.

00:01:19.464 --> 00:01:20.300
- [Priscilla] We're so excited.

00:01:20.300 --> 00:01:22.201
We can't wait to hear from you.

00:01:22.201 --> 00:01:25.252
(soft rock music)

